== 前身 ==
{{Main|Google+}}
2011年6月底，Google公司推出社交网络服务Google+。虽然Google野心勃勃，企图以此打败竞争对手Facebook，成为第一大社交网站<ref name="Google+ User Number">{{cite web|url=http://www.techabouts.com/20-million-people-google-2/|title=More 20 Million People Use Google+|accessdate=2011-07-23|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110923091649/http://www.techabouts.com/20-million-people-google-2/|archivedate=2011-09-23}}</ref><ref name="New York Times article">The New York Times, "Another Try by Google to Take On Facebook", 28 June 2011 http://www.nytimes.com/2011/06/29/technology/29google.html?_r=1 {{Wayback|url=http://www.nytimes.com/2011/06/29/technology/29google.html?_r=1 |date=20110701150302 }}</ref>，并且在2013年1月份，曾超越Twitter，一度成為世界上第二大的社交網站。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.leiphone.com/google-plus-active-user.html|title=Google+成全球第二大社交网络 仅次于FB|accessdate=2013-06-24|work=雷锋网|date=2013-01-27|language=zh-hans|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130503164752/http://www.leiphone.com/google-plus-active-user.html|archive-date=2013-05-03|dead-url=no}}</ref>但在之后的几年，其用户参与度低，加上於2018年3月发现可能會導致數十萬名的使用者資料外洩潛在的軟體漏洞<ref name="wall street journal">{{cite web|url=https://www.wsj.com/articles/google-exposed-user-data-feared-repercussions-of-disclosing-to-public-1539017194|title=Google Exposed User Data, Feared Repercussions of Disclosing to Public|work=The Wall Street Journal|date=2018-10-08|first1=Douglas|last1=MacMillan|first2=Robert|last2=McMillan|accessdate=2018-10-08|subscription=yes|language=en-US|issn=0099-9660|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181008170012/https://www.wsj.com/articles/google-exposed-user-data-feared-repercussions-of-disclosing-to-public-1539017194|archive-date=2018-10-08|dead-url=no}}</ref>，但Google没有在发现漏洞时主动告知用户，而在后来才承认存在漏洞<ref>{{cite web|title=洩50萬用戶個資竟還隱匿　谷歌宣布關閉Google+|url=https://tw.appledaily.com/new/realtime/20181009/1444249/|access-date=2018-10-09|date=2018-10-09|publisher=台灣蘋果日報|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190216064100/https://tw.appledaily.com/new/realtime/20181009/1444249/|archive-date=2019-02-16|dead-url=no|quote=Google內部人員則在今年3月發現漏洞後作出補救，不過公司內部開會決定，不把這件事通知用戶，避免聲譽受損，或成為監管機構的針對對象。Google當時向管理層分析，如果對外公布相關消息，令監管機構Google愈來愈對有興趣，甚至可能成為臉書的「劍橋分析洩密事故」翻版。}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Google for months kept secret a bug that imperiled the personal data of Google+ users|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/technology/2018/10/08/google-overhauls-privacy-rules-after-discovering-exposure-user-data/?noredirect=on&utm_term=.c311c70a7862|access-date=2018-10-09|date=2018-10-08|publisher=The Washington Post|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181009092914/https://www.washingtonpost.com/technology/2018/10/08/google-overhauls-privacy-rules-after-discovering-exposure-user-data/?noredirect=on&utm_term=.c311c70a7862|archive-date=2018-10-09|dead-url=no|quote=Google discovered the Google+ security bug in the same month that Silicon Valley rival Facebook was facing massive scrutiny over its role in allowing people affiliated with political consultancy Cambridge Analytica to collect data on 87 million users — an incident that led to demands that Facebook chief executive Mark Zuckerberg testify on Capitol Hill.|author1=Craig Timberg|author2=Renae Merle|author3=Cat Zakrzewski}}</ref>。Google决定在2019年4月2日关停消费者（个人）版本的Google+。个人用户可以在关停前下載並遷移他們的資訊；企業版則加入 [[Google_Workspace|Google Workspace]] 重新設計<ref name="project strobe">{{cite web|url=https://www.blog.google/technology/safety-security/project-strobe/|title=Project Strobe: Protecting your data, improving our third-party APIs, and sunsetting consumer Google+|first=Ben|last=Smith|date=2018-10-08|accessdate=2018-10-08|work=Google|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181008172414/https://www.blog.google/technology/safety-security/project-strobe/|archive-date=2018-10-08|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.blog.google/technology/safety-security/expediting-changes-google-plus/|title=Expediting changes to Google+|last=Thacker|first=David|date=2018-12-10|website=Google: The Keyword (company blog)|language=en|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181210233906/https://www.blog.google/technology/safety-security/expediting-changes-google-plus/|archive-date=2018-12-10|dead-url=yes|access-date=2018-12-11}}</ref>。

== 产品发展 ==
最初产品名为「Google+ for G Suite」，是[[Google+|Google+]]企業版結束後的後繼服務。

2019年4月10日，Google+ for G Suite更名为Google Currents，进入[[軟件版本週期#Beta|Beta测试阶段]]<ref>{{cite web |title=Introducing Currents, the newest G Suite app |url=https://gsuiteupdates.googleblog.com/2019/04/currents-for-gsuite.html |website=G Suite Updates Blog |publisher=Google |accessdate=2020-08-14 |language=en |date=2019-04-10 |archive-date=2019-06-08 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190608084610/https://gsuiteupdates.googleblog.com/2019/04/currents-for-gsuite.html |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.macobserver.com/news/google-currents-enterprise/|title=Google Currents is the Reanimated Corpse of Google+|date=2019-04-11|website=The Mac Observer|accessdate=2019-10-30|archive-date=2020-08-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200818031922/https://www.macobserver.com/news/google-currents-enterprise/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.techtimes.com/articles/241320/20190413/google-is-back-from-the-dead…-sort-of.htm|title=Google+ Is Back From The Dead … Sort Of|first=Carl|last=Velasco|date=2019-04-13|website=Tech Times|accessdate=2019-10-30|archive-date=2019-04-14|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190414161510/https://www.techtimes.com/articles/241320/20190413/google-is-back-from-the-dead%E2%80%A6-sort-of.htm|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://social.techcrunch.com/2019/04/10/with-consumer-g-dead-currents-hopes-to-make-waves-in-the-enterprise/|title=With consumer G+ dead, Currents hopes to make waves in the enterprise|accessdate=2019-10-30}}</ref>。2020年7月6日，Google Currents正式上线。
<ref>{{cite web |title=Currents to become generally available on July 6, 2020, replacing Google+ for G Suite |url=https://gsuiteupdates.googleblog.com/2020/06/google-currents-ga.html |website=G Suite Updates Blog |publisher=Google |accessdate=2020-08-14 |language=en |date=2020-06-22 |archive-date=2020-10-24 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201024022535/https://gsuiteupdates.googleblog.com/2020/06/google-currents-ga.html |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Peters |first1=Jay |title=Google Plus is officially gone after its mobile apps are rebranded as Google Currents |url=https://www.theverge.com/2020/7/6/21314912/google-plus-gone-mobile-apps-currents-rebranded |accessdate=2020-08-14 |website=The Verge |date=2020-07-06 |language=en |archive-date=2020-12-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201206232115/https://www.theverge.com/2020/7/6/21314912/google-plus-gone-mobile-apps-currents-rebranded |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Venkatesh |first1=Abhay |title=Google+ finally dies, makes way for Google Currents for G Suite users |url=https://www.neowin.net/news/google-finally-dies-makes-way-for-google-currents-for-g-suite-users/ |accessdate=2020-08-14 |website=Neowin |date=2020-07-06 |language=en |archive-date=2020-11-28 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201128092412/https://www.neowin.net/news/google-finally-dies-makes-way-for-google-currents-for-g-suite-users |dead-url=no }}</ref>

